DSA Algorithms Notes for Interviews | Sahil Hans | 26 comments
If you start revising just ONE DSA pattern every day, your interview confidence will look very different in 30 days. Most people dont get rejected because theyre bad at coding.   They get rejected because they cant explain their thinking. Interviews dont reward memorization.   They reward clarity, logic, and problem-solving depth. Thats why strong DSA foundations change everything. Not just to solve problems, but to: break problems into steps   choose the right approach   analyze time & space   communicate solutions confidently  Power move for beginners    1) Stop chasing random questions.   2) Start mastering patterns.   3) Focus on *why* an approach works, not just *what* works. Interview truth:   Even if your solution isnt perfect,   a clear explanation can still get you through. Master patterns, not questions.   One pattern = dozens of problems unlocked. Save this cheatsheet.   Revisit weekly.   Let your fundamentals do the heavy lifting.
